Each tetrahedron has four oxygen atoms, and each oxygen atom forms a bridge to another tetrahedron. Since each oxygen is shared between two tetrahedra, each of the four oxygen atoms in a given tetrahedron connects it to one other tetrahedron. Therefore, each silica tetrahedron is connected to four other tetrahedra.

